.TH man 8 "27 October 2016" "0.1.0" "mkscreen man page"
.SH NAME
mkscreen \- create a new screen session from a configuration file
.SH SYNOPSIS
mkscreen \fIconfig\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I mkscreen
is a simple alias to "screen \-U \-c \fIfile\fP \-S \fIsessionname\fP" with
tab completion. Just stash your configs in ~/.config/screen/ and you're ready
to go.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP 5
.B \-l
list all available configurations
.SH SEE ALSO
screen(1)
.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
.SH AUTHOR
thosbot (thomas@em7b5.net)
